    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Gabor Peterdi was a Hungarian-born American painter and graphic artist.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>Spanning 1939 to 1969, the 
        
        <emph render="bold">Gabor Peterdi Papers</emph> comprises 
reproductions of artwork, writings and memorabilia of the Hungarian-born 
American painter and graphic 
artist (b. 1915).  With the exception of two typescript book manuscripts, 
the entire collection consists of printed material which documents 
Peterdi's professional career.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Artwork</emph> consists of reproductions of Peterdi's works.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> include published articles and essays, typescripts 
for Peterdi's Great Prints of the World and Printmaking: Methods Old 
and New, and miscellaneous printed 
comments by Peterdi on his work.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Memorabilia</emph> includes articles about Peterdi (1955-1968), an 
extensive collection of exhibition catalogs and announcements for his 
one-man (1959-1968) and group 
shows (1939-1969), periodical reviews (1956-1966), and an assortment 
of brochures, flyers, reports, and miscellaneous printed material in 
which the artist is mentioned.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Writings are arranged alphabetically by type and then title.  Memorabilia is arranged alphabetically by type.  </p>
    </arrangement>
